; satsang-flip-witness.form -- agent board plus satsang protocol around the native public gate.
;
; Ask:
;   Use the agent board and the satsang protocol to embody the flip as witnessed
;   and knowable truth.
;
; Standing distinction:
;   The witnessed truth is not "ordinary traffic has moved." The witnessed truth
;   is narrower and stronger: the header-gated public canary moved, selected the
;   native kernel, returned a decision receipt, kept rollback available, and left
;   ordinary no-header traffic on fanout-python.
;
; High-level structure:
;   agent-board
;     claim: codex takes the satsang flip witness scope before editing.
;     share: durable learning points back to this file after validation.
;     nature: liquid coordination, not the permanent record.
;
;   satsang-circle
;     welcome: the question "can the flip be witnessed as true?" is admitted.
;     witness: honored voices count; projection is dropped; silence is whole.
;     survives: affirmations outnumber dissent, while dissent remains visible.
;     boundary: the circle witnesses the offered outside and never claims to
;       pierce the interior of a cell.
;
;   public-gate-canary
;     treatment: X-Form-Native-Public-Gate selects native-kernel.
;     control: no-header traffic remains fanout-python.
;     receipts: decision and rollback receipts are part of the witnessed fact.
;     reversible: removing the header or disabling the route row returns traffic.
;     boundary: ordinary_traffic_flip_performed remains false.
;
; Recipes that shifted:
;   before: flip as permission, proof, or hesitation.
;   after: flip as witnessed observation with reversible truth boundaries.
;
;   before: agent board as chatter.
;   after: agent board as the live witness carrier: claim, validate, share.
;
;   before: satsang as teaching.
;   after: satsang as an executable truth protocol:
;     welcome question -> gather attestations -> drop invasion -> preserve
;     silence and dissent -> survive by many vantages -> keep boundary exact.
;
;   before: ordinary no-header movement was the only imagined flip.
;   after: the canary movement itself is a true flip cell, and the ordinary
;     move waits only for sustained observation, not for self-trust.
;
; Executable surface:
;   form/form-stdlib/satsang-flip-witness.fk
;   form/form-stdlib/tests/satsang-flip-witness-band.fk
;
; Proof command:
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/channel-interface.fk form-stdlib/satsang.fk form-stdlib/satsang-flip-witness.fk form-stdlib/tests/satsang-flip-witness-band.fk
